The paper discusses the technical and operational aspects of Internet Exchange Points (IXPs) and their role in shaping the Internet ecosystem. This makes it highly likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. The paper also touches upon security and innovation aspects of IXPs, which could place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) categories, respectively. Additionally, the paper discusses the differences among IXPs in different regions, which could make it relevant to the Computer Communications (cs.CC) category. Finally, the paper also discusses the impact of IXPs on the Internet marketplace, which could place it in the Information Theory (cs.IT) category.
